deck: A penal facility apart of the Chaos! Comics mythos. Established in the late 1870's, Widmark acted as a detention facility housing the worst of the worst criminals in the state. It was also popular staging grounds for the repetitive return of Evil Ernie.
description:
A state side national internment stockade housing some of the most vile criminals the United States had ever tried, processed and executed. Moments before his rebirth a prison inmate who found a familiar button fell deathly sick, as said prisoners roommate was slated for execution his dead body became the new host for a reborn Evil Ernie.

In newer publishing the prison was featured in a Texan environment, where Ernest Fairchild was counted among a host of other ne'er do wells imprisoned for various crimes and atrocities. He was slated as its youngest prisoner on death row in all but 60 yrs since the prisons construction.

It was also here on June, 6th, 2011 where Evil Ernie was born the night Ernest was executed. The penitentiary itself was nuked in The White house's vain hope of culling the problem he represented before it escalated further, resulting instead in the murder of psychiatrist Dr. Thomas and many of its inmates. Some of whom were later reanimated serving under the leadership of fellow prisoner Rick Young later going as Homicide.

deck: A heavily guarded underground prison in the Laptev sea.
description:
Temho-Metya prison is a highly guarded facility beneath the Laptev sea. It is home to an unknown number of Metahumans and of the Annihilation Brigade. This is where they freed the Metahuman known as Hack who later joined the Suicide Squad after Captain Boomerang's untimely demise.

The Black Vault

Amanda Waller sends out the Suicide Squad to retrieve a cosmic item that came into possession of the Russians. The Squad was greeted by an infantry on their way to locating the item. They seek the help of a prisoner named Hack who leads them to the location. On their arrival, they realize that the item is actually a portal to the Phantom Zone holding General Zod as prisoner. During the encounter, General Zod incinerates Captain Boomerang thus leaving the rest of the squad to fight for their lives. Shortly after, the Annihilation Brigade tries to prevent them from stealing the portal. Rick Flag manages to push back General Zod back to the portal and seconds later they were back in Belle Reve after Hack used her powers to teleport the squad and the portal through the internet.
